claim.claim-text:
1. A method of pushing a single meat object through a netting chute, comprising:
piercing a target meat object with a pin extending from a pusher head;
contacting an outer surface of the target meat object with the pusher head;
automatically pushing the target meat object with the pusher head through a netting chute using at least one reciprocally-acting actuation cylinder operably connected to the pusher head; and
enclosing the target meat object in netting pulled off the netting chute in response to the automatically pushing step as the target meat object exits the netting chute.
